               <desc type="building-data" xml:lang="en">
                  <p source="#bibl000063-2">
                     [Jin Dynasty] The base of the hall is made of stone with a height of 1.5 meters. The hall is three bays wide and four rafters deep with a single-eave overhanging-gable roof (xuanshan 悬山顶).  Inside of the hall, there are four rafters (chuanfu 椽栿) and the space are equally divided into two parts by three columns (fenxincao 分心槽). The tops of the eaves pillars (yanzhu 檐柱) are rounded with a sharp narrowing. On top of the front eaves pillar, there are 5-puzuo (铺作) bracket sets (dougong 斗拱) with double descending cantilever (xia ang 下昂). On the other hand, the back eaves pillar only has single cantilever (ang 昂) and single perpendicular bracket arm (chaogong 抄栱). There is only one intercolumnar bracketing (bujian puzuo 补间铺作) in the central bay (dangxinjian 当心间). The Door and windows are built under the front eaves. The central bay has a single-panel door (banmen 板门) and the two secondary bays have mullioned windows (zhilingchuang 直棂窗). 
                  </p>
               </desc>  
